import lucid.optvis.objectives as objectives
import samplevis
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [2]:
# Import a model from Lucid's modelzoo.
model = models.InceptionV1_slim()
model.load_graphdef()
In [3]:
# Specify activation objective. For either neuron/channel/layer.
# In this case, it is channel 0 of Mixed_5b layer of InceptionV1-Slim.
obj = objectives.channel("InceptionV1/InceptionV1/Mixed_5b/concat", 0)
In [4]:
# Run sampling on the specified model and objective.
samples = samplevis.render(model, obj, hmc_opts=dict(num_results=10, num_burnin_steps=0, num_steps_between_results=100))
In [5]:
# Display all samples.
for sample in samples: plt.imshow(sample); plt.show()
